// Semantic direction:
// scott_domener: Scott (1970) — complete partial orders where least fixed points model recursion.
// dcpo: a poset (D, ⊑) where every directed set {xᵢ} has a least upper bound ⊔ᵢxᵢ.
// kontinuerlige_funksjoner: f: D → E preserving directed suprema — the morphisms of domains.
// kleene_fast_punkt: ⊥ ⊑ f(⊥) ⊑ f²(⊥) ⊑ ... converges to fix(f) = ⊔ fⁿ(⊥).
// scott_induktjon: to prove P(fix f), show P(⊥) and P(d) → P(f(d)) for admissible P.
// admissible_predikat: P closed under directed suprema — needed for Scott induction.
// algebraisk_domene: every element is the supremum of the compact elements below it.
// full_abstraction: denotational equality = observational equivalence — PCF model challenge.
// lazy_liste: a stream is a greatest fixed point; productive definitions yield infinite data.
// mu_typer: μX.F(X) is the least fixed point of F in the domain — e.g., μX.(1 + A × X) = List A.
// CPS_transformasjon: continuation-passing style makes control flow explicit in the semantics.

// Primitive flow:
// rekursiv_funksjon = fast_punkt(λf. kropp_med_f)
// fast_punkt(F) = ⊔ { F^n(⊥) | n ∈ ℕ }
// rekursiv_type μX.F = colim(⊥ → F(⊥) → F(F(⊥)) → ...)

